<L>__{exterior the grim house evening}
<A>__{simon hangs from the garbage truck as it comes up the street and pauses in front of his house. he jumps down and the truck barrels away.}
<L>__{interior fay's room evening}
<A>__{simon taps at the door. she looks over at him and he sees she's been crying. he comes into the room and she sits up on the edge of the bed.}
<C>__{simon}
<D>__{did you see him?}
<C>__{fay}
<D>__{he came by this afternoon.}
<C>__{simon}
<D>__{did you talk?}
<C>__{fay}
<D>__{no.}
<A>__{he comes over and sits beside her. he thinks a moment, then...}
<C>__{simon}
<D>__{you've got to tell him, fay.}
<C>__{fay}
<D>__{he thinks i'm a slut.}
<A>__{and she starts crying again. simon awkwardly touches her shoulder, then moves his hand away. fay pulls herself together, sniffles and goes into the bathroom.}
